Comment: 0,0:03:46.92,0:03:46.92,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:226920,226920}Part A
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.04,0:03:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:227045,229131}Marie… please smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.13,0:03:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:229131,232759}Why, Marie?\NWhy won't you smile at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.51,0:03:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:233510,235596}Please, open your eyes, Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.88,0:03:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:235888,237347}Father…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.37,0:04:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:264374,266043}This is your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.04,0:04:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:266043,269838}You killed Marie.\NYou ruined the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.34,0:04:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:272341,276220}You killed Marie and\Ndestroyed the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:279097,280349}Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.34,0:04:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:280349,283727}Get out of my house.\NEveryone out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.72,0:04:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:283727,285979}It is my house.\NGet out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.48,0:04:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:286480,288190}Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.19,0:04:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:288190,289399}Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.39,0:04:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:289399,293528}This is my house. None of you\Nare welcome here. Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.52,0:04:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:293528,294655}Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.03,0:04:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:296031,297824}What are you doing?\NWe have to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.20,0:04:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:298200,299868}Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.86,0:05:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:299868,302412}Get out of my house!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.70,0:05:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:302704,305832}Don't come near me. Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.83,0:05:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:305832,308252}Leave, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.67,0:05:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:311672,314091}– Get out of here…\N– Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316385,317010}Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.01,0:05:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:317010,321056}Get out…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.40,0:05:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:336405,339199}Mr. Andréa,\NI can show you the way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.19,0:05:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:339199,340575}What? Gaston?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.57,0:05:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:340575,344830}There is a secret passage\Nthat only I and my master knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.83,0:05:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:344830,345789}Follow me, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.99,0:05:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:346999,348166}Come on, Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.58,0:05:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:348583,349918}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.41,0:05:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:350419,352379}Everyone, follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:352379,353839}Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:354089,355716}Isabelle, you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.21,0:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:357217,358093}Isabelle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.30,0:06:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:358302,361096}No! I'm not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.09,0:06:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:361096,364975}I will not leave my father alone.\NI'm staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.47,0:06:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:365475,367769}Isabelle, come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.39,0:06:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:368395,370731}I'll decide what to do myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.73,0:06:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:370731,374192}Andréa, if you want to defend Paris,\Nbe my guest. But I'm staying here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.19,0:06:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:374192,376611}I will not leave\NMother and Father behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.98,0:06:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376987,377988}Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.98,0:06:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:377988,381199}Go now! Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.19,0:06:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:381199,384661}Andréa, you go first.\NI'll take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.66,0:06:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:384661,387456}You're not coming\Nwith us, Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.45,0:06:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:387456,391168}I'm sorry, Andréa, but as you know,\NI serve the Versailles government.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.46,0:06:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:391460,392627}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.17,0:06:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393170,395255}I still want to believe\Nin the French army.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.96,0:06:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395964,397132}I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.30,0:06:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:399301,401428}Then, talk some sense\Ninto Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.98,0:06:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:412981,415734}Everyone should\Nbe dead by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.57,0:07:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:420572,422991}Isabelle. Are you sure\Nthat you want to stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.57,0:07:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:424576,425827}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.62,0:07:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:427621,428872}I don't know…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:433627,436088}Why?\NWhy is this happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.08,0:07:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:436088,439132}Victor, explain it to me.\NWhat is this all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:443929,445430}Hands up, traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.88,0:07:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:445889,448225}Watch your mouth! Do you have\Nany idea who you're talking to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.35,0:07:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:449351,450769}Captain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.35,0:07:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:452354,456691}{\i1}Flames, raging like Léon's anger,\Ncompletely consumed the Rostains' estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.85,0:07:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:457859,461863}{\i1}The Rostain family fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.19,0:07:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:463198,464282}My master…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.28,0:07:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:464282,465450}My mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.67,0:08:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:484678,489349}{\i1}A few days later,\Nat the cemetery in Versailles
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.34,0:08:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:489349,493061}{\i1}a funeral was held\Nfor Léon and Marie Rostain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:493728,497023}{\i1}Since the Rostain family became\Ninfamous as traitors to the nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.02,0:08:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:497023,500902}{\i1}not many people\Ncame to the funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.54,0:08:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:518545,520755}Look, it's the daughter\Nof these subversives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.75,0:08:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:520755,524593}She's one cold piece of work.\NShe didn't even shed one tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.59,0:08:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:524593,527262}What did you say?\NWould you like to say it again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.26,0:08:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:527262,531475}Ah, I just meant that\Nshe's very strong, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.68,0:08:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:531683,532809}You dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.72,0:08:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534728,536104}Jean, leave him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.19,0:09:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:539191,542152}Please, don't make a scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.86,0:09:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:586863,589908}{\i1}The death of Marie and Léon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.90,0:09:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:589908,592911}{\i1}and with it, the fall\Nof the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.28,0:09:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:593286,597499}{\i1}Isabelle still found it all\Nvery hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.16,0:10:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:599167,603797}{\i1}However, the cold rain\Nkept pouring endlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.79,0:10:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603797,608718}{\i1}as if to remind Isabelle that\Nthe recent events really took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.70,0:10:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:632701,634369}Isabelle…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.25,0:10:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:643253,646381}How was the Rostains' funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.38,0:10:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:646381,648592}It must have been\Ngrandiose, no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.80,0:10:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:648800,650260}What is it that you want, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.88,0:10:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:650885,655515}This morning I received a secret letter\Nfrom Prussia. Here, read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.44,0:11:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:664441,665525}This… This is…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.11,0:11:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:667110,670322}Soon we will launch\Nan attack on Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.32,0:11:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:670322,673867}Within a short time we shall clean\Nthis city of the villains who occupy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.95,0:11:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:675952,679581}We will attack from this side,\Nand Prussia will strengthen us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.58,0:11:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679581,683418}Because we will approach from the south,\Nthey will be like rats in a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.71,0:11:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:683710,688506}You want to join the enemy and launch a\Njoint attack on the capital? Are you for real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.50,0:11:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:688506,694512}That's right. The people who occupy Paris\Nraise their fists to their own government.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.51,0:11:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:694512,697891}They pose a threat to every country,\Nlet alone Prussia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.89,0:11:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:697891,700894}As such, Prussia is more than\Nwilling to cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.89,0:11:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:700894,704147}Mr. Thiers, the people of Paris\Nare French, just like us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.48,0:11:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:704481,707776}You are wrong. The people\Nof Versailles are the real French.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.77,0:11:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:707776,709444}Not these knaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.44,0:11:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:709444,712781}Captain Langlois, you will\Ncommand the main attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.78,0:11:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:712781,716284}You want to make me\Nkill Paris citizens?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.28,0:11:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:716284,719329}The goal is to win back\Nthe capital and our properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.32,0:12:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:719329,723083}Anyone who objects shall not be spared,\Nnot even a woman or a child. Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.12,0:12:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:724125,725502}I have to refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.50,0:12:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:725502,726836}Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.08,0:12:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:727087,729130}I fight for France.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.13,0:12:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:729130,732175}My hands will not kill\Nmy French brothers and sisters!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:732467,735011}Disobedience means betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.38,0:12:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:735387,738765}I will not betray the people of France,\Neven if it means betraying you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.76,0:12:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:739766,741601}So be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.60,0:12:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:741601,744104}Panza!\NArrest Captain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.10,0:12:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:744104,746648}For treason, I sentence him\Nto death by the firing squad.
Comment: 0,0:12:32.69,0:12:32.69,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:752696,752696}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.07,0:12:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:754072,756991}The firing squad? For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.36,0:12:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757367,762122}Versailles doesn't need you\Nanymore, Captain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.12,0:12:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:762122,763456}Panza.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.50,0:12:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769504,772757}Mr. Thiers, as a soldier\Nof the French army,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.75,0:12:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:772757,775468}I demand a legal trial\Nin front of the court martial.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.46,0:12:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:775468,778179}Captain Langlois, our attack\Non Paris will begin any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.17,0:13:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:778179,780974}I'm sorry, but we can't afford it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.97,0:13:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:780974,784269}And besides, I believe that\Nyou might know a bit too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:784936,786479}Thiers…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.47,0:13:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:786479,789315}Scoundrels like you\Nare the real enemy of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.69,0:13:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:789691,793820}I decide who is the enemy\Nof France and who is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.82,0:13:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:793820,795196}Escort him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.19,0:13:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795196,796281}Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.28,0:13:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:796281,798032}Hands off!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.36,0:13:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:798366,800827}I can go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.84,0:13:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:820847,822682}Isabelle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.68,0:13:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:822682,824434}Jean, I don't want to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.43,0:13:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:824434,828146}Oh, stop it. In such circumstances\Nit is best to talk as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:828146,830064}I want to see your smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.06,0:13:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:830064,833318}If it makes you laugh,\NI can even try to do a handstand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:13:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:833318,835945}Please, tell me.\NWhat can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.94,0:13:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:835945,837113}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.11,0:14:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:837113,841659}So cold! Come on, there must be something.\NPlease tell me what it is. It can be anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.95,0:14:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841951,844704}Jean, leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.70,0:14:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:844704,848917}I am the daughter of a traitor.\NMy house and property were confiscated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:848917,851961}You deserve more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.96,0:14:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:851961,854047}You'd better\Nstay away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.04,0:14:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:854047,857342}Come on, now.\NWho I spend time with is my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.17,0:14:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:858176,860053}Why are you so stubborn?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.05,0:14:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:860053,862138}Please, leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.72,0:14:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:862722,864098}Fat chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.09,0:14:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:864098,865975}What are you going to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.39,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:866392,867519}I'm going back to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:867519,868603}To Paris?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.77,0:14:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:869771,873566}Isabelle from Paris goes to defend it.\NI see you've regained your fighting spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.56,0:14:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:873566,875902}It's not quite like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.90,0:14:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:875902,879239}I just can't stand it here\Nin Versailles any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.23,0:14:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:879239,881699}Our mansion in Paris\Nis the only place I have—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:881699,884035}Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.32,0:14:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:884327,887372}Miss, terrible news!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.83,0:14:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:887831,888832}Jeanne?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:889457,892544}Mr. Victor has been\Narrested for treason!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.87,0:14:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:892877,893920}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.92,0:14:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893920,897590}That's not all.\NHe's going to be shot tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.59,0:14:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:897590,899008}Shot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:902178,903638}He's going to be shot…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.30,0:15:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:907308,908935}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.52,0:15:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:913523,915859}What will I do without Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.85,0:15:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:915859,918528}No… I don't want\Nto think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.94,0:15:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919946,922031}What to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.03,0:15:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:922031,924158}I'm sick of it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.29,0:15:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:932292,934627}Miss Isabelle,\Nplease remain calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.00,0:15:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:935003,937005}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.00,0:15:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:937005,940508}Isabelle, let's meet here\Ntoday at midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.50,0:15:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:940508,941885}Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.30,0:15:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:944304,946222}I'll give you a gift,\Nthe best you ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.98,0:15:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:953980,956608}I probably won't be\Ncoming back any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.07,0:16:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:967076,969704}Marie… Françoise…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.70,0:16:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:969704,971873}Brigitte… Sylvie…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.87,0:16:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:971873,976044}Yvette… Joanne… Delphine…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.04,0:16:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:976044,978963}Ha, I'm quite popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.96,0:16:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:978963,981382}But I didn't get even one\Nfrom Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.44,0:16:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:998441,999692}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.06,0:16:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1000068,1004572}We should be living at Versailles now,\Na life free of any worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.57,0:16:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004572,1006866}What went wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1006866,1012372}But know that no matter what happens,\Nor how bad it will be, I will never leave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.66,0:16:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1012664,1016542}Isabelle, I am going to save\Nthe man you love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.54,0:16:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1016542,1018878}For you, I can do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.87,0:17:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1018878,1020213}Just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.58,0:17:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1020588,1022590}I always keep my word.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.02,0:17:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1040024,1041484}Young master?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.85,0:17:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1041859,1044320}My master called for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.32,0:17:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1044320,1045863}Gotcha. I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.95,0:17:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1049951,1051786}Did you call me, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.78,0:17:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051786,1053454}Ah, Jean. Would you like\Nto eat with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.45,0:17:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1053454,1056207}Unfortunately, I'm leaving soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.20,0:17:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1056207,1058960}Oh? Ah yes, you are\Nprobably going to a ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.96,0:17:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1058960,1060461}Uh… Yes, yes I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.46,0:17:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1060461,1062630}I understand. Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.63,0:17:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1062630,1066968}I'm just asking you not to hang out\Nwith that Isabelle of the Rostains.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1066968,1068261}Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.26,0:17:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1068261,1070805}Yes, Father.\NIt will be as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.80,0:17:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1070805,1073641}Perfect. You can go now, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.64,0:17:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1073641,1075059}Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.56,0:17:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1076561,1078354}{\i1}Adieu and goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.70,0:18:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1095705,1097749}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.49,0:18:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1098499,1100585}Move away from the window\Nas far as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1101127,1103421}Jean? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.00,0:18:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1104005,1107216}We'll talk later. When I count\Nto ten, I'll blow up the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.55,0:18:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1107550,1109761}Ten. Nine. Eight. Seven. Six.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.76,0:18:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1109761,1112138}Five. Four. Three. Two. One!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.93,0:18:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1117935,1119145}Thank you, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.68,0:18:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1119687,1121939}I have prepared horses for us.\NFollow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1122315,1124067}– There!\N– They're running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1124067,1126611}They're escaping!\NThey're climbing the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.86,0:18:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126861,1129363}Three… Two… One!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133868,1135703}After them!\NDon't let them escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.66,0:19:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138664,1141793}Hell, so much more to climb!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.79,0:19:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1141793,1144003}Jean, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.71,0:19:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1144712,1145922}Don't let them escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.30,0:19:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151302,1152220}Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.22,0:19:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1153221,1155973}Damn! I will show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.85,0:19:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1157850,1159977}They'll escape us!\NAfter them! Fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.97,0:19:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1159977,1160978}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.48,0:19:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1164482,1166442}Open the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1169278,1170696}{\i1}Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.50,0:19:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1182500,1184710}Jean! Did you do all this\Nall by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.71,0:19:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1184710,1187421}Yes. I can do quite a lot\Nif I only apply myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.04,0:19:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1189048,1191217}Thank you.\NBut why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.21,0:19:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1191217,1193886}Isabelle needs you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.88,0:19:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1193886,1195221}Isabelle?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.22,0:19:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1195221,1197932}You must take her to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.93,0:19:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1197932,1199225}But, Jean…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.22,0:20:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1199225,1203187}Honestly, now that I saved you, I wouldn't\Nmind if you disappeared somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.18,0:20:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1203187,1206149}But Isabelle…\NShe loves you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.73,0:20:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1207733,1209777}Man, what a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.19,0:20:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1210194,1212655}Jean, but you\Nsurely know that…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.94,0:20:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1212947,1215491}Doesn't matter.\NLet's just get the hell out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.25,0:20:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1227253,1229755}Who would've thought that\Nthis rascal would beat us to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.75,0:20:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1229755,1231883}Nice one, kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.38,0:20:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1235386,1237805}All right.\NWe'd better hurry as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.80,0:20:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1237805,1240391}The time has come.\NIt is time to fight for Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.39,0:20:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1240391,1242143}We will take our capital back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.14,0:20:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1242143,1243853}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.98,0:20:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1254989,1256115}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.15,0:20:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1257158,1257825}Jean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.15,0:20:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1258159,1259827}Here's the gift I promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.74,0:21:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1261746,1262872}Victor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.87,0:21:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1262872,1264457}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.99,0:21:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1264999,1266584}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.75,0:21:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270755,1272965}Isabelle, I'm going to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.80,0:21:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1274800,1278888}I finally understood\Nwhat I should really protect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.88,0:21:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278888,1281766}It is Paris.\NIt is the heart of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.93,0:21:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1282934,1284101}I'm going with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.39,0:21:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1284393,1286771}No. There will be\Nfighting everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.77,0:21:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1286771,1289857}It's too dangerous. I want you\Nto stay here and live happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.27,0:21:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1290274,1293194}No way. I will never\Nknow happiness here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.19,0:21:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1293194,1295571}Victor, please, take\Nme with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.03,0:21:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1296030,1297907}I'm begging you, Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.44,0:21:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1298449,1301327}Take me… Take me\Nwith you to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.32,0:21:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1301327,1302495}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.33,0:21:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1304330,1306207}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.62,0:21:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307625,1310044}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.88,0:21:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1314882,1316884}Hop on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.30,0:21:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1317301,1318177}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.22,0:22:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1319220,1321347}Please, take me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.34,0:22:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1321347,1325059}I don't have anywhere to go\Nwithout the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.05,0:22:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1325059,1326519}Jeanne?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.51,0:22:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1326519,1328437}You can come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.43,0:22:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328437,1330481}Jean, are you coming\Nwith us, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.89,0:22:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1330898,1332775}I got used to the gunfire by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.77,0:22:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332775,1336529}Versailles got too cramped\Nfor me as well, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.94,0:22:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1336946,1339615}Let's go!\NDirection – Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.61,0:22:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1339615,1340783}Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.37,0:22:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1344370,1348374}{\i1}"Let's go to Paris."\N"Let's take back our city!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.66,0:22:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1348666,1352211}{\i1}Andréa, Irma, Gaston…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.87,0:22:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1352878,1356048}{\i1}Isabelle, Victor, Jean…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.25,0:22:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1357258,1359260}{\i1}Finally, maid Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.59,0:22:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1360594,1366434}{\i1}Over the clatter of horses' hooves,\Nthey all thought about what awaited them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.10,0:23:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1375109,1380448}{\i1}However, Paris was completely\Nsurrounded by the Prussian army,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.44,0:23:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1380448,1387413}{\i1}and in Versailles, French troops commanded\Nby Thiers were already preparing to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.66,0:23:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1388664,1393252}{\i1}The capital of France was stuck\Nbetween a rock and a hard place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.25,0:23:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1393252,1395463}Kill! Kill them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.46,0:23:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1395463,1399091}Death to all who stand against us.\NParis is ours!
